comments: Butler (MIA) firms up in a screening position in Wagner's (ORL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
As Vincent (MIA) goes underneath the screen, Carter Jr. (ORL) extends a forearm into him and delivers contact.
Banchero (ORL) initiates contact to Butler's (MIA) wrist that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Banchero (ORL) slides his pivot foot.
Adebayo (MIA) moves from point A to point B and initiates contact to Banchero's (ORL) body, affecting his SQBR.
Banchero (ORL) hooks Adebayo (MIA) prior to his shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Butler (MIA) during the drive.
Harris (ORL) reaches across Herro's (MIA) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Butler (MIA) extends his leg upon releasing the shot attempt at the basket and initiates the marginal contact with Banchero (ORL).
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Vincent's (MIA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Herro (MIA) legally contests Harris's (ORL) jump shot attempt.

As Carter Jr. (ORL) gathers the rebound, Butler (MIA) reaches in and makes contact with the ball and any arm contact is marginal.  Separately, Adebayo (MIA) reaches in and makes incidental contact with Carter Jr.'s hand on the ball.  Once the ball is loose, marginal arm contact occurs when Adebayo follows through.
Fultz (ORL) and Vincent (MIA) mutually engage and disengage during the throw-in.

Replay review of the foul called on Fultz (ORL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Fultz initiates contact to Vincent's (MIA) face, affecting his ability to control the loose ball.
Butler (MIA) reaches in and initiates contact to Fultz's (ORL) front that affects his SQBR.
Butler (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Banchero (ORL) during the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact that occurs with Banchero (ORL) during his driving shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) engages with Butler (MIA) during the throw-in and the contact is marginal.
Strus (MIA) grabs the rebound and a timeout is immediately signaled for by Miami, but is not recognized by officials until there are 1.5 seconds remaining.
Harris (ORL) legally contests Butler's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) legally contests Butler's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) moves alongside of Butler's (MIA) path to the basket and marginal body contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Strus's (MIA) arm is not in a vertical position as Wagner (ORL) splits the defenders but the arm contact during his driving shot attempt is marginal.
Vincent (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position defending Fultz's (ORL) drive to the basket and Fultz loses control of the ball on his own.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Fultz (ORL) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Strus (MIA) legally contests Harris's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) steps out of bounds.
Banchero (ORL) commits a take foul on Butler (MIA).
Wagner (ORL) wraps Herro (MIA) and affects his FOM prior to the release of the throw-in.
